# Theme Naming & Governance

## Required name layers (must all match)

| Layer | Example |
| --- | --- |
| Theme package directory | `packages/theme-immersive-showcase` |
| Theme ID (in `site.config.ts`) | `immersive-showcase` |
| CSS root class on `<body>` | `.theme-immersive-showcase` |
| CSS class prefix | `.ims-*` (alias of `immersive-showcase`, must be documented inline) |
| Theme documentation | `docs/themes/immersive-showcase.md` |

## Theme ID rules

- Lowercase kebab-case ASCII only. **Technical theme IDs MUST NEVER contain Chinese characters.** Chinese names belong only in docs and registries.
- Use industry-neutral or visual-pattern names: `immersive-showcase`, `industrial-grid`, `luxury-residence`, `catalog-trade`, `technical-b2b`, `minimal-corporate`.
- Forbidden: `theme1`, `new-theme`, `beautiful-theme`, version-numbered or self-praising names.
- The theme ID and the `packages/theme-<id>` directory name must be byte-for-byte identical.

## Governance

- A theme package owns ONLY its own `.<prefix>-*` CSS classes and scopes every rule under `.theme-<theme-id>` so multiple themes can coexist without collisions.
- All theme packages MUST export the same section component contract required by `apps/site-builder/src/components/SectionRenderer.tsx`. The set of exported component names and their prop shapes is the cross-theme contract.
- If a theme does not visually support a given section type, it MUST still ship a safe fallback component (e.g. minimal stacked layout) for that section instead of breaking the build.
- A new theme MAY import `@factory/ui` and shared types/utilities from `@factory/validators`. A new theme MUST NOT import from any other theme package; themes are siblings, not derivatives.
- Every new theme MUST ship with `docs/themes/<theme-id>.md`.
- Every new theme MUST be registered in BOTH places:
  - `apps/site-builder` theme registry source code, and
  - `docs/registries/theme-registry.md`.
- A new theme MUST also be added to the `theme` enum in `packages/validators/src/site-config.schema.ts`.
- Themes MUST NOT hardcode any company name, navigation list, image path, email, phone number, or copy text. All such data flows from `site.config.ts` props or page section JSON.
- Per-site visual differentiation goes through `site.config.ts` data only (e.g. `themeTokens`, `brand.logo`). NEVER write per-site CSS inside a theme package.
